ury or death.","Position the ABS modulator/ECM to its bracket and tighten the two fixings to ","9 Nm",".","Position the left hand bracket to the ABS modulator/ECM, do not fully tighten the fixing at this stage.","ABS modulator/ECM bracket","Left hand bracket fixing","Underside fixings","Carefully manoeuvre the ABS modulator/ECM and bracket assembly to the frame.","Fit the right hand ABS bracket fixing and washer but do not fully tighten at this stage.","Fixing","Washer","Fit the left hand fixing and washer but do not fully tighten at this stage.","Fit the top fixing and washer, tighten the fixing to ","9 Nm",".","Tighten the top and right hand fixings to ","9 Nm",".","Fixing (left hand side)","Fixing (top)","Washers","Tighten the left hand ABS modulator/ECM bracket fixing to ","9 Nm",".","Fixing (left hand side)","Left hand bracket","Coolant expansion tank","Incorporating new washers to either side of the unions, fit the brake lines to the ABS modulator as noted for removal.","Tighten the new anti rotation moulding fixing to ","3 Nm",".","Brake line unions","Anti rotation moulding","Tighten the union bolts to ","25 Nm",".","Refit the breather cover cable guide and tighten the new fixings to ","3 Nm",".","Breather cover guide","Fixings","Refit the harnesses as shown below.","Starter lead","Rectifier/regulator lead","Gear position sensor lead","Crankshaft position sensor lead","Engine subharness","Negative battery lead","Damage to the connector pins may result if an attempt to fit the connectors incorrectly is made.","If the lever is not fully over to the rear position, it is possible that the connector may not fully engage into its socket.","Connect the ABS module connector (see ","ABS Modulator Electrical Connector Disconnect/Reconnect and Pin Numbering",").","Position the spigots on the expansion tank cover to the grommets.","Press firmly to secure the cover.","Expansion tank cover","Spigots","Grommets","Grasp the cover and make sure that it is fully retained.","Use only DOT 4 specification brake fluid as listed in the general information section of this manual. The use of brake fluids other than those DOT 4 fluids listed in the general information section may reduce the efficiency of the braking system leading to an accident.","Observe the brake fluid handling warnings given earlier in this section of the manual.","It is dangerous to operate the motorcycle with defective brakes; you must have your authorised Triumph Dealer take remedial action. Failure to take remedial action may reduce braking efficiency leading to loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","Rear Brake Caliper","Back bleed the rear brake master cylinder (see ","Bleeding the Rear Brakes",").","Rear brake caliper bleed (see ","Bleeding the Rear Brakes",").","Rear brake final bleed procedure (see ","Bleeding the Rear Brakes",").","Fit the caliper retaining fixings, and tighten to ","28 Nm",".","Rear brake caliper","Caliper mounting fixings","Rear brake hose union bolt","Bleed screw","Attach the ABS wheel speed sensor harness to its clamps under the swinging arm as noted for removal.","ABS wheel speed sensor harness","Rear brake hose","Clamps","Refit the rear brake hose cover to the swinging arm and tighten the new fixings to ","4 Nm",".","Chain rubbing strip","Lower fixing","Brake caliper conditioning (see ","Bleeding the Rear Brakes",").","Check for correct brake operation. Rectify as necessary.","Fit the rear wheel (see ","Rear Wheel - Installation",").","Front Brake Caliper","Remove the cable tie securing the front brake lever.","Brake lever","Cable tie","Back bleed the rear brake master cylinder (see ","Bleeding the Front Brakes",").","Fit the front brake caliper (see ","Front Brake Caliper - Installation",").","Front brake caliper bleed (see ","Bleeding the Front Brakes",").","Front brake final bleed procedure (see ","Bleeding the Front Brakes",").","Front brake caliper conditioning (see ","Bleeding the Front Brakes",").","Check for correct front and rear brake operation. Rectify as necessary.","It is dangerous to operate the motorcycle with defective brakes.","The fault must be checked and rectified by a competent person with the specialist knowledge and technical understanding of motorcycles, such as an authorised Triumph dealer.","Failure to follow the advice above may lead to loss of motorcycle control which could result in serious injury or death.","Perform the following operations:","Throttle Body - Installation","Airbox - Installation","Chassis Electronic Control Module - Installation","Fuel Tank - Installation","Battery - Installation","Seats - Installation"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","createdAt":"2024-04-15T13:51:46.899Z","updatedAt":"2024-04-15T13:51:46.899Z","__v":0}